      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial, though often debated, concept that protects fundamental rights from government overreach, ensuring the government can't infringe on core liberties even if it follows proper procedure. This doctrine has been vital in protecting personal freedoms, such as the right to privacy and bodily autonomy, against legislative intrusion. It serves as a powerful check on government power, safeguarding individual rights that are inherent to liberty.",
      "source": "target",
