    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a very strong way to frame it. I think my students will really connect with the idea of the judiciary being a \"bulwark.\" Since I'm trying to build a lesson that focuses on the necessity of these protections, could you help me draft a few discussion questions for the class? I want the questions to push them to realize that sticking to a strict, literal reading of the text often fails to protect people's basic rights in a modern society.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
