      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "How can a government truly be considered \"free\" if its laws can arbitrarily strip away fundamental aspects of personal autonomy, even if those laws are technically written into the code? If we only adhere to the most literal text, how do we protect rights that society has evolved to recognize as essential for human dignity? When does a strict reading of the law become a tool for oppression rather than a shield for liberty?",
      "source": "target",
